      {
         "id": "SECTION_conclusion",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Conclusion</h3>To count all the musical instruments above the bird in <b>Figure 1</b>, our fingers will look like this:</p><table class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th>Left hand</th><th>Description</th><th>Right hand</th></tr>  <tr><td><img id=\"img26\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img26', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/1Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised, and index of the left hand raised.</td><td><img id=\"img27\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img27', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr></table><p class=\"desc\"><b>Table 2</b>: Couting musical instruments in <b>Figure 1</b>.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"lab\"><b>Practice 1: Couting around</b><br />Using your fingers, count some objects around you.</p><p>As we have seen, our hands can help us count. But how can we count a quantity larger than the number of fingers we have? We will begin to explore this in the next text.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
